div.p: Without error code stub does: push 0 then push int_no With error code CPU already pushed it; stub does only: push int_no Both paths arrive at isr_common_stub with identical stack layout. The C handler always finds err_code at frame->err_code (offset +36). For no-error-code exceptions, frame->err_code == 0. Why normalize? Without this, the C struct offsets would differ by 4 bytes between the two cases requiring separate structs or runtime branching before every field access. The dummy push makes one universal interrupt_frame_t possible.
